1
00:00:08,458 --> 00:00:10,000
[KUNUDONS gasping]

2
00:00:10,083 --> 00:00:11,541
[KUNUDONS scream]

3
00:00:11,625 --> 00:00:13,250
[GAKUSHU]
Ice Prison.

4
00:00:15,041 --> 00:00:17,291
[GAKUSHU] Hmph. Perhaps next
time you'll think twice

5
00:00:17,375 --> 00:00:19,375
before withholding information.

6
00:00:24,083 --> 00:00:25,291
[KOYAMA chuckles]

7
00:00:25,375 --> 00:00:26,625
[KOYAMA]
Asano!

8
00:00:26,708 --> 00:00:28,041
We have a lead on the
Demon King's whereabouts!

9
00:00:28,125 --> 00:00:29,625
Do you?

10
00:00:29,708 --> 00:00:31,791
Yes. Word on the street is that
there's a new teacher in town.

11
00:00:31,875 --> 00:00:34,416
He's holding court at the
old satellite campus.

12
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:35,833
[GAKUSHU]
Wait.

13
00:00:35,916 --> 00:00:38,208
I figured out his
secret location first!

14
00:00:38,291 --> 00:00:39,750
[OTHERS]
This was a competition?!

15
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:42,083
[GAKUSHU] Hyah! To the
mountain, my soldiers!

16
00:00:42,166 --> 00:00:44,125
First one there gets
dibs on using the bath!

17
00:00:44,208 --> 00:00:46,291
[OTHERS]
You're on horseback!

18
00:01:47,166 --> 00:01:49,625
[SUGAYA] Dude, d'you hear
about the paladins?

19
00:01:49,708 --> 00:01:51,083
Of course I have!

20
00:01:51,166 --> 00:01:53,833
It's the Big Five and they're
headed to this village.

21
00:01:53,916 --> 00:01:55,041
What's a paladin?

22
00:01:55,125 --> 00:01:56,583
A company of skilled knights.

23
00:01:56,666 --> 00:01:59,625
They fight for the Goddess
under oath from the Pope.

24
00:01:59,708 --> 00:02:01,541
The Big Five are
an elite subgroup

25
00:02:01,625 --> 00:02:04,916
said to be without peer
in the entire realm.

26
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,625
[KORO-SENSEI] Very good, Isogai.
You've done your homework.

27
00:02:07,708 --> 00:02:09,458
[HAYAMI] Sure, but why are
they on the way here?

28
00:02:09,541 --> 00:02:11,041
[KORO SENSEI]
Hmm...

29
00:02:11,125 --> 00:02:13,166
Why don't we dedicate ourselves
to gathering the relevant intel

30
00:02:13,250 --> 00:02:14,958
we couldn't scrounge
up last week?

31
00:02:15,041 --> 00:02:16,541
[NAGISA]
Sounds hard.

32
00:02:16,625 --> 00:02:18,958
[KORO-SENSEI] No worries! I have
just the person to help us out!

33
00:02:19,041 --> 00:02:20,000
[giggles]

34
00:02:20,083 --> 00:02:21,666
Hiya, boys!

35
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:24,666
The Seductive Witch?
You sure that's a good idea?

36
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:25,833
Ugh.

37
00:02:25,916 --> 00:02:27,208
We're prepared to offer
her a full pardon

38
00:02:27,291 --> 00:02:30,250
in exchange for her services
as a magic teacher.

39
00:02:30,333 --> 00:02:32,875
Poor darling.
The octopus needed help.

40
00:02:32,958 --> 00:02:35,500
So out of the kindness
of my widdle heart,

41
00:02:35,583 --> 00:02:38,208
I schmoozed my way through
the nightlife scene.

42
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:40,458
"Hey," I said to every bar fly.

43
00:02:40,541 --> 00:02:43,333
"What's a girl gotta do
to get the latest gossip?

44
00:02:43,416 --> 00:02:45,291
C'mon, spill."

45
00:02:45,375 --> 00:02:46,791
[CLASS]
What kind of teacher are you?!

46
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:49,083
Whatever it takes to dig
up the dirt on these guys.

47
00:02:49,166 --> 00:02:50,750
Sad old men love the attention.

48
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:52,750
Boy, do they ever.

49
00:02:52,833 --> 00:02:54,458
Wait, did you
both go with her?

50
00:02:54,541 --> 00:02:55,791
Of course.

51
00:02:55,875 --> 00:02:56,958
Hey, if you're gonna learn
the art of seduction,

52
00:02:57,041 --> 00:02:58,500
might as well study with a pro.

53
00:02:58,583 --> 00:02:59,500
D'you go, too?

54
00:02:59,583 --> 00:03:01,625
Yeah, I was there
as a chaperone.

55
00:03:01,708 --> 00:03:03,833
Mostly for the moral support.
And the food.

56
00:03:03,916 --> 00:03:06,125
[KORO-SENSEI] I fulfilled
the role of wing-woman.

57
00:03:06,208 --> 00:03:07,500
[CLASS] Way to lower
their effectiveness.

58
00:03:07,583 --> 00:03:09,416
No beer goggles
are thick enough.

59
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:11,958
Lot a' Big Five gossip
on the tavern circuit.

60
00:03:12,041 --> 00:03:13,083
And?

61
00:03:13,166 --> 00:03:14,708
Why would an elite
subgroup of paladins

62
00:03:14,791 --> 00:03:17,375
hoof it to a backwater
nowhere like this?

63
00:03:17,458 --> 00:03:18,583
You don't know?

64
00:03:18,666 --> 00:03:21,166
They're making a B-line
for E-class, silly.

65
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:22,416
[CLASS]
Huh?

66
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,625
Ye olde rumor mill's all a-buzz.

67
00:03:24,708 --> 00:03:27,166
Everybody seems to know
the Demon King's here.

68
00:03:27,250 --> 00:03:28,708
We have to play it safe.

69
00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:31,500
The only other human being aware
of our mission is the Pope.

70
00:03:31,583 --> 00:03:33,041
If the rumors are confirmed,

71
00:03:33,125 --> 00:03:35,041
we'll all be arrested for
harboring the enemy.

72
00:03:35,125 --> 00:03:37,666
No! I'm too young
to go to jail!

73
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:41,208
So we'll just find a way to hide
Koro-sensei's true identity.

74
00:03:41,291 --> 00:03:43,083
It's our only option
at this point.

75
00:03:43,166 --> 00:03:45,166
[KORO-SENSEI] Eek! Why are
you staring at me like that?

76
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:47,750
Oh, man. Hope no one
counts your legs.

77
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:49,583
Maybe I should rip off
some tentacles.

78
00:03:49,666 --> 00:03:51,500
[KORO SENSEI]
That seems a little extreme!

79
00:03:51,583 --> 00:03:52,958
[HINANO] First impressions
are everything.

80
00:03:53,041 --> 00:03:54,791
[MIMURA] I vote we go
for the serious look.

81
00:03:54,875 --> 00:03:56,291
[SUGAYA]
And a nose while we're at it.

82
00:03:56,375 --> 00:03:57,541
[TOKA]
And hair! Gotta have hair!

83
00:03:57,625 --> 00:03:58,750
[NAKAMURA]
No offense, Commander,

84
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:00,875
but can you and the bi--
uh--witch get lost?

85
00:04:00,958 --> 00:04:01,708
[IRINA]
Hey!

86
00:04:01,791 --> 00:04:02,875
[KARASUMA]
What did I do?!

87
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:04,083
[MIMURA, SUGAYA]
Koro-Q!

88
00:04:06,041 --> 00:04:08,166
What a surprise.
First place goes to me.

89
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:10,583
[SEO] Real talk: You kinda
had an unfair head start.

90
00:04:10,666 --> 00:04:12,500
[ARAKI] You know what
didn't help? The ice traps!

91
00:04:12,583 --> 00:04:14,541
If you wanna take a bath
before the rest of us so badly,

92
00:04:14,625 --> 00:04:15,666
just do it!

93
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:18,041
Come, stop trying
to cloud the issue.

94
00:04:18,125 --> 00:04:21,166
We must take on a challenge
in dead earnest or not at all.

95
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:24,208
If a paladin fails,
so too does mankind.

96
00:04:24,291 --> 00:04:27,458
Whoever the foe is, we bring
all our strength to bear.

97
00:04:27,541 --> 00:04:30,333
Such is our duty as the
protectors of the realm!

98
00:04:30,416 --> 00:04:32,875
[OTHERS] Are you really
choosing bath salts right now?

99
00:04:32,958 --> 00:04:34,583
Well, he has a point.

100
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:36,208
Yes! Inspiring speech!

101
00:04:36,291 --> 00:04:38,375
Spoken just like a
born leader, sir!

102
00:04:38,458 --> 00:04:39,708
Yeah!

103
00:04:39,791 --> 00:04:42,041
Let's show that cowardly
Demon King who's the boss!

104
00:04:42,125 --> 00:04:43,166
[ALL yell]

105
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:43,750
[GAKUSHU]
Wait.

106
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:44,750
[OTHERS]
Uh?

107
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:47,166
I will find the
Demon King first!

108
00:04:47,250 --> 00:04:49,250
We're not in competition
with each other!

109
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:50,458
[GAKUSHU]
We ride!

110
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:52,041
[OTHERS] You're the
only one with a horse!

111
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:53,208
[SEO]
Koro-Q.

112
00:04:55,125 --> 00:04:56,166
[NAKAMURA]
Mmm...

113
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:57,625
Meh, It'll do.

114
00:04:57,708 --> 00:04:59,458
Not bad, I guess?

115
00:04:59,541 --> 00:05:00,291
[HAYAMI]
Hey, Chiba.

116
00:05:00,375 --> 00:05:01,708
Want me to take over?

117
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:02,750
Look!

118
00:05:08,708 --> 00:05:09,958
[CLASS]
What is wrong with you?

119
00:05:10,041 --> 00:05:11,708
Ugh! This guy ever
heard of a door?

120
00:05:11,791 --> 00:05:13,166
This coming from you?!

121
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:15,000
[BIG FIVE]
Koro-Q!

122
00:05:15,083 --> 00:05:16,708
Soldiers! Sally forth!

123
00:05:16,791 --> 00:05:19,666
[OTHERS panting]

124
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:21,416
We are the Big Five.

125
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,875
Hark! For the Demon
King's time is nigh!

126
00:05:23,958 --> 00:05:26,916
So do you ride that horse
everywhere you go, or what?

127
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,458
[chuckles]

128
00:05:28,541 --> 00:05:31,375
Our intrepid captain prefers
to look down on scum, you see.

129
00:05:31,458 --> 00:05:32,916
Literally.

130
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:36,000
Nor is Asano truly satisfied
unless he's first in everything.

131
00:05:36,083 --> 00:05:37,541
Seriously.

132
00:05:37,625 --> 00:05:39,375
[SAKAKIBARA]
And I mean everything.

133
00:05:39,458 --> 00:05:40,375
Even the bath.

134
00:05:40,458 --> 00:05:41,750
[NAGISA]
With his horse?

135
00:05:41,833 --> 00:05:42,916
[KOYAMA]
And who else but he

136
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,083
gets the top bunk
in our five-bunk bed?

137
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:46,916
[NAKAMURA]
Whoa, you guys sleep together?

138
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,375
[NAGISA]
With his horse?!

139
00:05:48,458 --> 00:05:50,791
Huh. Your buddies are quick
to paint us a picture.

140
00:05:50,875 --> 00:05:53,500
Must be nice having
your own hype-men.

141
00:05:53,583 --> 00:05:54,916
They're just trying
to make the most

142
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,375
of the only episode they're in.

143
00:05:56,458 --> 00:05:58,666
What is that supposed to mean?

144
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:00,791
Ah. You must be our quarry.

145
00:06:00,875 --> 00:06:02,333
[KORO-SENSEI]
Whatever are you implying?

146
00:06:02,416 --> 00:06:04,000
Don't bother playing dumb.

147
00:06:04,083 --> 00:06:06,458
And now behold the Light Orb!

148
00:06:06,541 --> 00:06:08,583
Lo, the Goddess bestowed
this blessing upon us,

149
00:06:08,666 --> 00:06:10,708
that we might weaken
the Demon King!

150
00:06:10,791 --> 00:06:12,416
[KORO-SENSEI]
Uh-oh!

151
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,083
Take this!

152
00:06:16,208 --> 00:06:17,333
Sir! Look out!

153
00:06:17,416 --> 00:06:22,291
[KORO-SENSEI yelping]

154
00:06:29,166 --> 00:06:30,791
[gasps]

155
00:06:30,875 --> 00:06:32,875
[ALL]
Uhh...

156
00:06:34,083 --> 00:06:36,708
Um. What just happened?

157
00:06:36,791 --> 00:06:39,458
[KORO-SENSEI] My fault entirely.
I shouldn't have dodged.

158
00:06:39,541 --> 00:06:41,375
How could you even
dodge a key item?!

159
00:06:41,458 --> 00:06:43,083
[KORO-SENSEI]
I know, I know! All apologies!

160
00:06:43,166 --> 00:06:45,500
Let me fix it up for you!

161
00:06:45,583 --> 00:06:46,583
Yeah! Here we go! Good as new!

162
00:06:46,666 --> 00:06:49,083
What the hell is that thing?!

163
00:06:49,166 --> 00:06:50,166
[ARAKI, KOYAMA, SAKAKIBARA]
Now what?

164
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:51,666
[SEO]
Is this really the Demon King?

165
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,291
[KOYAMA]
The orb did react to him.

166
00:06:53,375 --> 00:06:56,458
Yes, but he's wearing glasses.
And can we talk about that hair?

167
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:59,083
His face seems
awfully round to me.

168
00:06:59,166 --> 00:07:01,958
Hey! Those supporting characters
are getting all the lines!

169
00:07:02,041 --> 00:07:03,708
Why do they get to
talk more than us?

170
00:07:03,791 --> 00:07:06,750
I have every possible monster
committed to my memory.

171
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:09,250
But he isn't covered
in any of the manuals.

172
00:07:09,333 --> 00:07:10,416
Well, you would know.

173
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:11,916
Wait.

174
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,333
I memorized them, too,
and I did it first.

175
00:07:14,416 --> 00:07:16,416
This isn't a competition!

176
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:19,166
Well, even so,
we've lost the orb

177
00:07:19,250 --> 00:07:21,250
so there's no telling
if it's him.

178
00:07:21,333 --> 00:07:24,333
Nonsense. We will
test him by strength.

179
00:07:28,958 --> 00:07:30,333
Ah!

180
00:07:30,416 --> 00:07:32,541
The Magic Frostblade that
Asano alone in all the world

181
00:07:32,625 --> 00:07:33,291
can conjure!

182
00:07:33,375 --> 00:07:34,666
[KARMA]
Weird.

183
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,125
I thought they'd be
harder to make.

184
00:07:36,208 --> 00:07:37,208
[KOYAMA yells]

185
00:07:37,291 --> 00:07:38,958
[MIMURA, SUGAYA shouting]

186
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:40,500
[FUWA sighs]

187
00:07:40,583 --> 00:07:42,333
Dial it back a little bit, guys.

188
00:07:42,416 --> 00:07:43,666
Hey, I have theory.

189
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:45,541
It's not that other
people can't conjure it,

190
00:07:45,625 --> 00:07:47,375
they just think it looks dumb.

191
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:49,750
Oh, I wouldn't be so confident.

192
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:52,041
Sure, you can create
your own Frostblade,

193
00:07:52,125 --> 00:07:55,250
but can you face
an armamentalist?

194
00:07:55,333 --> 00:07:57,416
[KORO-SENSEI] Okay, okay.
That's quite enough, boys.

195
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:58,750
Thank you.

196
00:07:58,833 --> 00:08:01,041
I'd like you fellas to be
on your way now, please.

197
00:08:01,125 --> 00:08:04,375
Unless of course you'd prefer me
to bring the Pope into this.

198
00:08:04,458 --> 00:08:05,208
[ALL gasp]

199
00:08:05,291 --> 00:08:08,166
[ALL]
No, not the Pope!

200
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:09,708
[CLASS]
Huh?

201
00:08:09,791 --> 00:08:10,375
[KARMA]
Wait!

202
00:08:10,458 --> 00:08:11,208
Is that him now?

203
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:12,791
[BIG FIVE scream]

204
00:08:12,875 --> 00:08:15,583
Sorry. False alarm. Hm?

205
00:08:15,666 --> 00:08:16,958
[CLASS]
Seriously?

206
00:08:17,041 --> 00:08:19,416
Wow you scared the Big
Five out of their minds.

207
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:21,833
How terrifying is
the Pope exactly?

208
00:08:21,916 --> 00:08:23,375
[KORO-SENSEI]
Just as I thought.

209
00:08:23,458 --> 00:08:24,958
Your little hunt
for the Demon King

210
00:08:25,041 --> 00:08:26,625
wasn't at the Pope's behest.

211
00:08:26,708 --> 00:08:28,250
The Big Five thought
to take matters

212
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:29,708
into their own hands, eh?

213
00:08:29,791 --> 00:08:30,875
Interesting.

214
00:08:30,958 --> 00:08:32,750
If the Church didn't
sanction this quest,

215
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:34,500
you gentlemen are
solely accountable

216
00:08:34,583 --> 00:08:36,000
for the havoc wrought today,

217
00:08:36,083 --> 00:08:38,000
not to mention
interrupting my class.

218
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:41,333
The Pope's attitude toward loose
cannons is less than kind.

219
00:08:41,416 --> 00:08:43,583
How might he react
to his hand-picked paladins

220
00:08:43,666 --> 00:08:45,833
going rogue, I wonder?

221
00:08:47,625 --> 00:08:50,333
[KORO-SENSEI] Something else it
behooves us to bear in mind.

222
00:08:50,416 --> 00:08:51,541
When last the Orb of Light

223
00:08:51,625 --> 00:08:53,458
was taken without
express permission,

224
00:08:53,541 --> 00:08:58,000
His Holiness is said to have
gone through the roof.

225
00:08:58,083 --> 00:08:59,958
You're in trouble
enough as it is.

226
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:03,500
The sooner you own up to
breaking it, the better.

227
00:09:03,583 --> 00:09:04,791
[ALL screaming]

228
00:09:04,875 --> 00:09:07,791
[NAGISA] Those faces
belong in the apocalypse!

229
00:09:07,875 --> 00:09:09,958
[GAKUSHU]
We shall withdraw.

230
00:09:10,041 --> 00:09:12,083
First one back to Kunugigaoka
gets to blame the others

231
00:09:12,166 --> 00:09:13,833
for breaking the Orb!

232
00:09:13,916 --> 00:09:15,708
[OTHERS]
Let us have your horse!

233
00:09:15,791 --> 00:09:16,708
[SAKAKIBARA]
Quit screwin' around!

234
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:18,916
[SEO]
We're not as fast as you!

235
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:21,291
[SUMIRE] Woohoo!
We just beat the Big Five!

236
00:09:21,375 --> 00:09:23,583
[HINANO] Wow, we didn't
even have to fight!

237
00:09:23,666 --> 00:09:25,083
[chuckles]

238
00:09:25,166 --> 00:09:26,500
[KORO-SENSEI]
Just goes to show you, class:

239
00:09:26,583 --> 00:09:30,083
Swords and sorcery pale
in comparison to good intel.

240
00:09:30,166 --> 00:09:32,666
[NAGISA] Information's
a handy weapon all right.

241
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:35,000
Only thing...

242
00:09:35,083 --> 00:09:35,916
[KORO-SENSEI]
Mew?

243
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:36,958
[KARASUMA]
You're on the hook

244
00:09:37,041 --> 00:09:38,375
for the witch's
reconnaissance fee.

245
00:09:38,458 --> 00:09:41,083
[KORO-SENSEI] Ah! How did she
